# TORVAN Medical Workflow Management System
# Commit Message Template for Medical Software Compliance

# Format: <type>[optional scope]: <description>
#
# Example: feat(inventory): add barcode scanning for medical devices

# Types:
# feat:       New feature
# fix:        Bug fix  
# docs:       Documentation changes
# style:      Code style changes (formatting, etc.)
# refactor:   Code refactoring without feature changes
# perf:       Performance improvements
# test:       Adding or updating tests
# chore:      Maintenance tasks, build process, etc.
# security:   Security-related changes
# medical:    Medical device specific functionality
# regulatory: Regulatory compliance changes
# compliance: General compliance modifications
# audit:      Audit trail or logging changes

# Subject line rules:
# - Use imperative mood ("add" not "added")
# - Keep under 50 characters
# - Don't end with a period
# - Capitalize first letter after colon (lowercase)

# Body (optional):
# - Explain WHAT and WHY, not HOW
# - Wrap at 72 characters
# - Reference issues: "Closes #123" or "Fixes #456"
# - Include medical/regulatory context when applicable

# Footer (optional):
# - Breaking changes: "BREAKING CHANGE: description"
# - Co-authored by: "Co-authored-by: Name <email>"
# - Regulatory references: "FDA-Reference: 21CFR820.70"
# - Risk level: "Risk-Level: Low|Medium|High"

# Medical Software Guidelines:
# - All commits are part of audit trail
# - Include sufficient context for regulatory review  
# - Reference quality management system when applicable
# - Consider patient safety impact in commit messages
# - Document any medical device classification changes